xhost +local:docker

docker run -it \
    --rm \
    -e DISPLAY=$DISPLAY \
    -e RUNNING_IN_DOCKER=1 \
    -v /tmp/.X11-unix:/tmp/.X11-unix \
    -v $HOME/.Xauthority:/root/.Xauthority:ro \
    -v $(pwd):/app \
    roster-app

```
Explanation:

-it: Interactive terminal (optional, helps for debugging).

--rm: Remove container after exit.

-e DISPLAY=$DISPLAY: Pass host X11 display to container for GUI.

-e RUNNING_IN_DOCKER=1: Flag so open_host() knows itâ€™s in Docker.

-v /tmp/.X11-unix:/tmp/.X11-unix: Share X11 socket for GUI forwarding.

-v $HOME/.Xauthority:/root/.Xauthority:ro: Allow authentication with host X server.

-v /path/to/your/project:/app: Mount your project folder into container.

python-tk-roster: Docker image name (build it from your Dockerfile).

python main.py: Run your Tkinter app inside container.
```